# Next.js — Quality (Part 4)

## 24. SEO System

Use metadata API. Every page defines `metadata`. Include OpenGraph, canonical, sitemap.xml, robots.txt, JSON-LD.

```ts
export const metadata = {
  title: "Dashboard",
  description: "User dashboard",
  openGraph: { title: "...", description: "..." }
}
```

## 25. Performance

- **Code splitting**: Automatic per route.
- **Image**: `next/image` with `width`, `height`, `alt`.
- **Dynamic import**: `dynamic(() => import('./Chart'))`.
- **Caching**: `force-cache`, `revalidate`, `no-store` on fetch.
- **Memoization**: `useMemo`, `useCallback`, `React.memo`.
- **Virtualization**: `@tanstack/react-virtual` or `react-window` for long lists.
- **CLS**: Reserve space; skeleton matching content; image dimensions.

## 30. Accessibility

**Semantic tags:**

| Element | Use |
|---------|-----|
| `<header>` | Site or section header |
| `<main>` | Primary content (one per page) |
| `<nav>` | Navigation links |
| `<article>` | Self-contained content |
| `<section>` | Thematic grouping |
| `<aside>` | Sidebar / tangential |
| `<footer>` | Site or section footer |

- Semantic HTML; `aria-label` for icon buttons; `<label htmlFor>`; `aria-invalid`, `aria-describedby`.
- `aria-label` for icon buttons; `<label htmlFor>`; `aria-invalid`, `aria-describedby`.
- Keyboard nav; focus trap in modals; restore focus on close.
- Color contrast; axe + Lighthouse.
- `jest-axe` in component tests:

```ts
import { axe, toHaveNoViolations } from 'jest-axe'
expect.extend(toHaveNoViolations)
test('no a11y violations', async () => {
  const { container } = render(<Button>Submit</Button>)
  expect(await axe(container)).toHaveNoViolations()
})
```

## 31. Testing

Unit: Vitest + React Testing Library + `userEvent`. Prefer `getByRole`, `getByLabelText`.

**MSW**: `src/mocks/handlers.ts`, `server.ts`; `server.listen()` in `vitest.setup.ts`. Use `@testing-library/jest-dom` for matchers.

**E2E** (`e2e/`): `tests/`, `playwright.config.ts`, `global-setup.ts`. Page Object pattern.

**Coverage** (`vitest.config.ts`):

```ts
coverage: { provider: 'v8', thresholds: { lines: 70 } }
```

**Fixtures**: `tests/fixtures/`; factories aligned with Zod schemas.

## 32. Linting & Prettier

ESLint: `next/core-web-vitals`, `prettier`. Prettier: semi: false, singleQuote, trailingComma: all.

## Regression tests & debugging

- **Framework**: Vitest + React Testing Library; E2E: Playwright.
- **Location**: Co-locate `*.test.tsx` or `__tests__/`; E2E in `e2e/` or `tests/`.
- **Commands**: `npm test`; `next lint` or `npm run lint`; `tsc --noEmit`.
- **Regression**: Add `test('handles [bug scenario] - regression', ...)` that would have caught the bug.
- **Verify**: `npm test` and `npm run lint` pass before commit.

## Checklist

- [ ] SEO: metadata API; OpenGraph; canonical; sitemap/robots.
- [ ] Performance: `next/image`; dynamic import; virtualization for long lists; CLS prevention.
- [ ] Accessibility: semantic tags; aria; keyboard; axe + Lighthouse.
- [ ] Testing: Vitest + RTL; MSW for API; E2E with Playwright; coverage thresholds.
